28/05/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Top officials of the BiH State Information and Protection Agency (SIPA) and police chiefs from BiH, Croatia and Serbia-Montenegro agreed to boost co-operation in fighting organised crime in the region, during a meeting Friday (26 May) in Sarajevo. 
According to SIPA chief Sredoje Novic, the group discussed specific issues related to collaboration with the UN war crimes tribunal and combating terrorism, organised crime, drugs and human trafficking. 
(Nezavisne novine, Dnevni avaz - 27/05/06)
